Quote: <i>poppy, Californian [=] eschscholtzia</i> [s] <i>Ibid.</i> 86 CALIFORNIAN POPPY (<i>Eschsholzia</i> [Eschscholtzia] <i>californica</i>), often called eschscholtzia, and sometimes Johnny-go-to-bed, on account perhaps of its nightcap-like calyces, is found in profusion on the shingly river-beds of the South Island.
